2.x : add strict ( ) operator for strong RS conformance __EoT__ This PR adds a new instance operator ` strict ( ) ` : Ensures that the event flow between the upstream and downstream follow the Reactive-Streams 1.0 specification by honoring the 3 additional rules ( which are omitted in standard operators due to performance reasons ) . * Â§1.3 : onNext should not be called concurrently until onSubscribe returns * Â§2.3 : onError or onComplete must not call cancel * Â§3.9 : negative requests should emit an onError ( IllegalArgumentException ) In addition , if rule Â§2.12 ( onSubscribe must be called at most once ) is violated , the sequence is cancelled an onError ( IllegalStateException ) is emitted . Note that the Reactive-Streams specification does n't have any sanction for violating Â§2.12 . The ` strict ( ) ` operator also replaces the test-only operators that were supporting the Reactive-Streams TCKs already .
